Clustering => Technique used to find groups of observations(clusters) that 
share similar characteristics. 
KmeansClustering is an Unsupervised Learning Algorithm for data classification. 

Kmeans begins with randomly chosen data points as proposed means of the 
data groups and iteratively recalculates new means in order to 
converge to a final clustering of the data points. 

When define value of K, ur telling the algorithm how many means or 
centeroids u want. 
k = 3 => 3 clusters 
Centeroid is a data point that represents the center of the cluster 
and it might not necessarily be a member of the dataset. 

How the algorithm works ?? 
1. K centeroids re created randomly based on pre defined value of K 
2. kmeans allocates every data pt in the dataset to the nearest centeroid 
3. kmeans recalculates the centeroids by taking the mean of all data points assigned 
to that centeroids cluster 
4. The algorithm iterates between steps 2 and 3 until some criteria is met 
